article.headline: Jones scores 20 points off bench, Lipsey adds 17 in No. 5 Cyclones' 87-52 win over IU Indianapolis
article.description: — Curtis Jones scored 20 points and Tamin Lipsey added 17 to lead No. 5 Iowa State past IU Indianapolis 87-52 on Monday night.

article.story: AMES, Iowa -- — Curtis Jones scored 20 points and Tamin Lipsey added 17 to lead No. 5 Iowa State past IU Indianapolis 87-52 on Monday night. It was Jones' second straight 20-point game off the bench and fourth in his two seasons with the Cyclones (3-0). Saint Mary's transfer Joshua Jefferson had his first double-double for Iowa State with 16 points and 10 rebounds. Keshon Gilbert had 11 points and eight assists, and Lipsey led the Cyclones with five steals. Paul Zilinskas led the Jaguars (2-3) with 16 points and Jarvis Walker added eight. Takeaways IU Indianapolis: The Jaguars are 0-17 against Top 25 teams and 0-2 this season versus power-conference opponents, having lost to Xavier 94-80 on Nov. 8. Iowa State: The Cyclones had four players score in double figures for the second time this season. They also had four do it against Mississippi Valley State. Key moment Jones made three of his four 3-pointers during a 13-0 run that put the Cyclones up 27-5 eight minutes into the game. Key stat Jefferson was 7 of 7 from the field and 2 of 2 from the free-throw line in his 26 minutes. Up next Iowa State heads to the Maui Invitational to take on No. 4 Auburn next Monday. IU Indianapolis travels to the Bulldog Bash in Huntsville, Alabama, to take on Coastal Carolina on Friday. ------ Get poll alerts and updates on the AP Top 25 throughout the season. Sign up here.
